  "response": "The Illuminati is a term that refers to different groups throughout history, but has become largely associated with conspiracy theories. Here are some key points:\n\n1. Historical origins:\n- The original Bavarian Illuminati was a secret society founded in 1776 by Adam Weishaupt\n- It was an Enlightenment-era group that opposed religious influence in public life and advocated for rational thinking\n- The group was banned by the Bavarian government in 1785\n\n2. Modern conspiracy theories:\n- Many conspiracy theories claim the Illuminati is a powerful, secretive organization controlling world events\n- Theories suggest they manipulate governments, economies, and global affairs\n- These claims are not supported by credible evidence\n\n3. Popular conspiracy beliefs:\n- Alleged control of global financial systems\n- Influencing political leadership\n- Orchestrating major world events\n- Membership of powerful global elites\n\n4. Current status:\n- No credible evidence exists of a contemporary, functioning Illuminati organization\n- The term is primarily used in conspiracy theories and popular culture\n- Most scholarly historians view modern Illuminati claims as unfounded\n\nWhile the original group was a real historical organization, current theories about a global, all-powerful Illuminati are considered baseless by experts.",
